Executive Profile
Thomas J. Edelman  Founder, Chairman of the Board and Chief Executive Officer, Bear Cub Investments, LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 7 Board Members in 7 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships66--
Background

		Mr. Thomas J. Edelman, also known as Tom, is a Managing Partner and Co-Founder of White Deer Energy. Mr. Edelman is the Founder of Bear Cub Investments, LLC and serves as its Chairman and Chief Executive Officer. Mr. Edelman was a Co-Founder of BioFuels Energy Corp. and served as its Principal Financial Officer until March 2007. Prior to forming White Deer, Mr. Edelman founded and/or managed a series of eight energy companies, creating significant value for investors ... over more than a 25-year period. Mr. Edelman founded Patina Oil & Gas Corp. in 1996 and served as its Chief Executive Officer and Chairman from 1996 to 2005. He served as the President of Patina Oil & Gas Corp. since December 2004. From 1988 to 2003, Mr. Edelman served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of Range Resources Corporation and also served as its Chairman from 1988 to 2003. He served as an Advisor to the Board of Range Resources Corp. until 2006. He was a co-founder of Range Resources. He co-founded Snyder Oil Corporation and served as its President, from 1981 to February 1997. From 1975 to 1981, Mr. Edelman served as a Vice President at The First Boston Corp. Energy Group and from 1975 to 1980, he served at Lehman Brothers Kuhn Loeb Inc. He served as an Associate at the firm. He has service as the President and Chief Executive Officer of several independent oil and natural gas companies and his knowledge and expertise of the oil and natural gas industry. In 2000, Mr. Edelman co-founded Bear Paw Energy LLC, serving as its Chairman. He has been the Chairman of Berenson & Company, Inc. since 2006. He served as the Chairman of BioFuels Energy Corp. since May 2006. He has been an Independent Director of Noble Energy, Inc. since May 2005. He serves as a Director of Lomak Petroleum Inc. He serves as a Director of Amerac Energy Corp., Leopard Acquisition Corp., and Command Petroleum Ltd. He serves as a Director at Berenson & Company and White Deer Energy II L.P. He has been a Director of Petroleum Heat and Power Inc. since October 1983. He serves as a Director at Paradise Music & Entertainment Inc. He serves as a Trustee of The Hotchkiss School. Mr. Edelman served as a Director of Snyder Oil Corp., from 1981 to February 1997 and Suncast Solar Energy, Inc. from October 1996 to December 20, 2000. He served as a Director at BioFuels Energy Corp. He served as a Director of Emerald Oil, Inc. from February 2013 to January 28, 2015. He served as a Director of Star Gas LLC since March 1999 and Petro Holdings Inc. since October 1983. He served as a Director of Star Gas Corp., from December 1993 to June 1995 and also from October 1995 to March 1999. He served as an Independent Director of PostRock Energy Corporation from September 2010 to October 30, 2015. Mr. Edelman served as a Director of Enterra Corp., from August 1994 to October 1995. He served as a Director of Weatherford Enterra, Inc. since March 11, 1997. He is the President and Chairman Emeritus of the Board of Lenox Hill Neighborhood House and a Member of the Board of Georgetown University. He is a Director of the Wildlife Conservation Society. He serves on the Advisory Council of Princeton University’s Department of Politics. Mr. Edelman holds an M.B.A. in Finance, Baker Scholar from Harvard University's Graduate School of Business Administration in 1975 and B.A. in Political Economy, magna cum laude from Princeton University in 1973.Read Full Background




