Insider Activity


Individual




Thomas Jeffery Edelman



Mr. Thomas J. Edelman is Independent Director at PostRock Energy Corp., Managing Partner at White Deer Management LLC, Independent Director at Noble Energy, Inc., Chairman at Bear Cub Investments LLC, President at Lenox Hill Neighborhood House, and Managing Partner at White Deer Energy LP. He is on the Board of Directors at PostRock Energy Corp., Noble Energy, Inc., The Hotchkiss School, Leopard Acquisition Corp., Berenson & Co, Inc., and Georgetown University.
Prior to forming White Deer in 2008, Mr. Edelman founded and managed a series of eight energy companies, creating significant value for investors over more than a 25 year period. He founded or co-founded Snyder Oil Corporation (now part of Devon Energy Corporation), Range Resources and Patina Oil and Gas (now part of Noble Energy, Inc.). He also co-founded Bear Paw Energy and Bear Cub Energy, both midstream companies based in the Rocky Mountains. Prior to 1981, he was a Vice President in The First Boston Corporation’s (now Credit Suisse) energy group and an associate at Lehman Brothers Kuhn Loeb Incorporated. He is currently a Director of Emerald Oil, Inc.
Mr. Edelman holds an MBA in Finance from Harvard Business School and a BA in Political Economy from Princeton University, magna cum laude.



