Ms. Todman died in January 2008. Her co-op was listed a few weeks later with Mr. Burger for $24 million. Within 10 days it was in contract to Mr. Edelman,  and it closed in May 2008.Mr. Edelman quickly put his old apartment at 770 Park on the market for $16.75 million, while he began renovations on the new space.But when the luxury real estate market sank along with the economy later that year, the listing was pulled. When it went back on the market earlier this month, the asking price had been cut by $6 million, or more than 34 percent.
